# Feature: Fixed species ($prefix) STRICT test — non-catalytic consumption
# Tests: $A stays constant even when a rule fires "A -> B" that would
#   normally consume A.  Companion to ft_clamped_species.bngl, where
#   the rule is catalytic (E on both sides) so conservation is
#   automatic regardless of Fixed support.
# Tier: base
# Expected: A_tot ≡ 100 for all t; B_tot grows linearly at rate k*A0 = 10/s.
#   At t=50, B_tot ≈ 500.
# If RM silently ignores Fixed/$: A decays exponentially at rate k=0.1,
#   at t=50 (t*k=5) A_tot ≈ 100*exp(-5) ≈ 0.67 and B_tot asymptotes
#   at ~99.3.  Divergence from NFsim is unambiguous.

begin model
begin parameters
    A0  100
    k   0.1   # /s
end parameters

begin molecule types
    A()
    B()
end molecule types

begin seed species
    $A()  A0   # $ = Fixed population — must not deplete
    B()   0
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  A_tot  A()
    Molecules  B_tot  B()
end observables

begin reaction rules
    # Non-catalytic: A on LHS but NOT on RHS.  With Fixed enforcement
    # A stays at A0; without enforcement A depletes.
    A() -> B()  k
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>50,n_steps=>50})
end actions

# invariant: conserved A_tot = 100
